AUDIO: 'The first is API exposure. This node is using header O credentials, which are handled securely by NAN. So, your API key isn\'t being hard-coded or sent visibly. Anytime you\'re using stored credentials like this, you\'re in good'

[12:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'shape. But here\'s what it would look like if it were wrong. If the templates ask you to manually paste your API key directly into the node, usually in like the headers or the body, like the node will work that way, but it\'s not secure. If you were to save the workflow or'

[12:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
